selection_reason: This team stands out with the highest projected 5GW score (352.2) and an excellent GW1 score (68.4). The 4-4-2 formation provides good balance between attack and defense. Key strengths include Salah as captain (very reliable and on penalties), Cole Palmer (Chelsea's focal point, on penalties), and strong midfield coverage. The team avoids over-reliance on injury-prone players and spreads risk across multiple teams. Chris Wood offers good value as a differential forward.

The 5-3-2 formation with Gvardiol provides extra defensive stability while maintaining strong attacking potential. High projected points (347.0) and solid GW1 score (67.4) indicate consistency. The inclusion of Man City defensive coverage through Gvardiol is shrewd as City has strong clean sheet potential. Similar core to Team 1 with Salah, Palmer, and Mbeumo provides proven point-scoring capability with minimal rotation risk.

BENCH2: David Mota Veiga Teixeira do Carmo (Nott'm Forest)
selection_reason: This team offers excellent value with a 4-4-2 formation and strong midfield quartet. The inclusion of Yoane Wissa provides a differential option from Brentford's attacking setup. While slightly lower projected points (344.6), the team structure allows for easy transfers and formation flexibility. Notable for avoiding overexposure to any single team while maintaining Salah and Palmer as core assets.
